Will Martin McGuinness be a guest at the Queen's Irish reception?
There is talk that the Queen will invite Martin McGuinness to the reception she is holding on March 25 for the 'Irish community'.
Queen Elizabeth II shakes hands with Northern Ireland Deputy First Minister Martin McGuinness Photo: PA	By Tim Walker
7:26AM GMT 08 Feb 2014
Comments
The Queen delights in her “all walks of life” lunches. Whether she will take such an approach to the reception she is holding on March 25 for the “Irish community,” ahead of the first state visit of Ireland’s president, Michael D Higgins, remains to be seen. Martin McGuinness, whose accomplices murdered Lord Mountbatten, the Queen’s cousin, shared a historic handshake with her when she visited Belfast in 2012. So is the Stormont Deputy First Minister on the guest list? Neither Buckingham Palace, nor McGuinness, will tell me. Least said “I know far too many fathers who have to grovel to their ex-wives for the odd evening or weekend with their children,” Ben Goldsmith observed on a social networking site. Did this mark the recommencement of public hostilities between him and his former wife Kate Rothschild, with whom he traded barbs after her affair with the rapper Jay Electronica. Related Articles
