WikiLeaks: Britain secretly advised Libya how to secure release of Lockerbie bomber
Ministers secretly advised Muammar Gaddafi’s Libyan regime how to secure the successful early release of the Lockerbie bomber, documents obtained by The Daily Telegraph have disclosed.
Image 1 of 3	Lockerbie bomber Abdelbaset al-Megrahi clasps the hand of Saif al-Islam Gaddafi, the Libyan leader's son, after arriving back in Tripoli Photo: AFP	Image 1 of 3	The Libyan Investment Authority was offered the option of $5bn of preferred shares in Goldman Sachs in an effort to appease senior Libyan officials angered by losses, the Wall Street Journal reported. Photo: EPA	Image 1 of 3	After Megrahi was released in August 2009, another American document records Gaddafi’s comments – which suggest that Prince Andrew, the UK’s trade envoy, may have played a role. Photo: REX	<
